ne 1999|accessdate=10 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206200228/https://mcgill.ca/architecture/people-0/aluminterviews/charney|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Moshe Safdie]] (MArch 1961) &ndash; architect of [[Habitat 67]], [[Marina Bay Sands]], [[Jewel Changi Airport]] and the [[Montreal Museum of Fine Arts]]<ref>{{Cite interview|url=https://www.mcgill.ca/architecture/people-0/aluminterviews/safdie|last=Safdie|first=Moshe|interviewer=Jim Donaldson|publisher=Peter Guo-hua Fu School of Architecture|title=Alumni Interviews|date=12 November 1997|accessdate=10 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206200432/https://mcgill.ca/architecture/people-0/aluminterviews/safdie|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Oberlander]] (BArch 1945) &ndash; architect and Canada's first professor of Urban and Regional Planning<ref>{{Cite interview|url=https://www.mcgill.ca/architecture/people-0/aluminterviews/oberlander|last=Oberlander|first=Peter|interviewer=Jim Donaldson|publisher=Peter Guo-hua Fu School of Architecture|title=Alumni Interviews|date=19 February 1998|accessdate=10 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206200254/https://mcgill.ca/architecture/people-0/aluminterviews/oberlander|archive-date=6 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Rami Bebawi (BSc[Arch] 1999, MArch 2001) &ndash; co-founder of [[KANVA Architecture]], 2017 Prix de Rome winner<ref name=Alumni2 /> \n*Randy Cohen (BSc[Arch] 1981, BArch 1982) &ndash; co-founder of Atelier Big City, 1998 Prix de Rome winner<ref name=AtelierBigCity />\n*[[Raymond Affleck]] (BArch 1947) &ndash; co-founder of [[Arcop]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cca.qc.ca/en/archives/225767/ray-affleck-fonds|title=Ray Affleck fonds|publisher=Canadian Centre for Architecture|accessdate=10 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629112217/https://www.cca.qc.ca/en/archives/225767/ray-affleck-fonds|archive-date=29 June 2019|ur